    • void SET_PLAYER_WANTED_LEVEL_NOW(Player player, BOOL p1) // 0xAF3AFD83
      Forces the wanted level to be applied to the specified player immediately.

      Call SET_PLAYER_WANTED_LEVEL with the desired wanted level, followed by SET_PLAYER_WANTED_LEVEL_NOW.

      Second parameter is unknown. Always false.

    • void SET_MAX_WANTED_LEVEL(int maxWantedLevel) // 0x665A06F5
      Sets the maximum wanted level the player can get.
      Ranges from 0 to 5.
      If the specified maxWantedLevel is below 0, the function does nothing. If it's 5 or above, the max wanted level will be set to 5.

      If the player currently has a wanted level greater than the specified maxWantedLevel, the player's current wanted level will not be decreased until the next wanted level update. Eg. when the player shoots.

    • BOOL IS_PED_IN_VEHICLE(Ped pedHandle, Vehicle vehicleHandle, BOOL atGetIn) // 0x7DA6BC83
      Gets a value indicating whether the specified ped is in the specified vehicle.

      If 'atGetIn' is false, the function will not return true until the ped is sitting in the vehicle and is about to close the door. If it's true, the function returns true the moment the ped starts to get onto the seat (after opening the door). Eg. if false, and the ped is getting into a submersible, the function will not return true until the ped has descended down into the submersible and gotten into the seat, while if it's true, it'll return true the moment the hatch has been opened and the ped is about to descend into the submersible.
    • BOOL IS_PED_IN_MODEL(Any p0, Any p1) // 0xA6438D4B
    • BOOL IS_PED_IN_ANY_VEHICLE(Ped pedHandle, BOOL atGetIn) // 0x3B0171EE
      Gets a value indicating whether the specified ped is in any vehicle.

      If 'atGetIn' is false, the function will not return true until the ped is sitting in the vehicle and is about to close the door. If it's true, the function returns true the moment the ped starts to get onto the seat (after opening the door). Eg. if false, and the ped is getting into a submersible, the function will not return true until the ped has descended down into the submersible and gotten into the seat, while if it's true, it'll return true the moment the hatch has been opened and the ped is about to descend into the submersible.

    • void TASK_ENTER_VEHICLE(Ped pedHandle, Vehicle vehicleHandle, int timeout, int seat, float p4, Any p5, Any p6) // 0xB8689B4E
      Makes the specified ped enter the specified vehicle. If the ped is already in a vehicle, or is on another seat, it will get out first.

      pedHandle: The ped to assign the task to.
      vehicleHandle: The vehicle the ped should get into.
      timeout: If getting into the vehicle takes longer than the timeout (in ms) the ped is warped into the vehicle.
      seat: The seat to get in on. -1 is driver, 0 is passenger, 1 is left rear, 2 is right rear.
    • void TASK_LEAVE_VEHICLE(Ped pedHandle, Vehicle vehicleHandle, int flags) // 0x7B1141C6
      Makes the specified ped leave the specified vehicle.

      pedHandle: The ped to assign the task to.
      vehicleHandle: The vehicle to leave.
      flags: Bitwise flags.
      None = 0,
      UnknownOrUnused0 = 1 << 0,
      UnknownOrUnused1 = 1 << 1,
      UnknownOrUnused2 = 1 << 2,
      UnknownOrUnused3 = 1 << 3,
      WarpOut = 1 << 4, // Warps out of the vehicle.
      UnknownOrUnused5 = 1 << 5,
      Unknown6 = 1 << 6,
      UnknownOrUnused7 = 1 << 7,
      LeaveDoorOpen = 1 << 8, // Leaves the door open after getting out.
      UnknownOrUnused9 = 1 << 9,
      UnknownOrUnused10 = 1 << 10,
      UnknownOrUnused11 = 1 << 11,
      BailOut = 1 << 12, // Bails out of the vehicle if it's moving. Without this flag, the character will still get out immediately, but without falling.
      UnknownOrUnused13 = 1 << 13,
      UnknownOrUnused14 = 1 << 14,
      UnknownOrUnused15 = 1 << 15,

    • Any GET_GROUND_Z_FOR_3D_COORD(float x, float y, float z, float *groundZ) // 0xA1BFD5E0
      Gets the ground elevation at the specified position. Note that if the specified position is below ground level, the function will output zero!

      x: Position on the X-axis to get ground elevation at.
      y: Position on the Y-axis to get ground elevation at.
      z: Position on the Z-axis to get ground elevation at.
      groundZ: The ground elevation at the specified position.
